## Context

- All 5 phases complete. Source code in src/cancer/rb1_loss_pancancer_dependency_atlas/, outputs in output/cancer/rb1-loss-pancancer-dependency-atlas/phase{1-5}/.
- Phase 1: Multi-modal RB1-loss classifier. 493 RB1-loss, 1239 intact lines, 19 qualifying cancer types. CDK4/6 dependency validation passed.
- Phase 2: CDK2 strongest ROBUST SL (d=-0.524). AURKA, MYBL2 also ROBUST. CCNE1-amp subgroup extreme CDK2 dependency (d=-2.236). CDK4/6 negative controls validated. Task #840: regenerated summary with corrected negative control labels (VALIDATES for positive-d significant results instead of UNEXPECTED).
- Phase 3: Genome-wide screen found 23 gained, 33 lost dependencies. 16 priority targets including novel ATAC complex hits (TADA2A, YEATS2, ZZZ3). 9 shared with CDKN2A, 30 RB1-unique.
- Phase 4: PRISM validation. Trilaciclib validates as negative control. 3 selective, 6 resistant drugs in genome-wide screen.
- Phase 5: TCGA integration. ~125K estimated RB1-loss patients/yr US. Top priority: SKCM, Osteosarcoma, Bladder. CDK2 trial alignment mapped.
- No remaining tasks. Project ready for analyst/validation.
